  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 12 high, 5 medium, 22 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO); plus 9 other bases. 5 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT), Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR). Network hotspots: Marche (AOI/LIPY), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Shirak (LWN/UDSG). Primary drivers: very low visibility, low cloud base and fog / freezing fog. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Marche (AOI/LIPY), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Shirak (LWN/UDSG) and 9 others.",
